==English==

===Noun===
{{Wikipedia}}
'''day for night'''

#''Filmology.'' A cinematographic technique in which a crew films in a high-contrast situation, typically in the early morning or late afternoon, with a blue filter, causing the scene to look as if it were shot in moonlight.

===Adverb===
'''day for night'''

#''Filmology.'' In the daytime, with a blue filter, causing the scene to look as if it were shot in moonlight.
#:''The Sandcrawler scene in ''Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope'' was shot day for night.''